this needs to be present regardless of whether or not it exists on dbus.  Your current code doesn't handle that.

This isn't optional in the redfish spec, but is optional on dbus.  You need to fill in status regardless of whether it exists on dbus.

It actually is not required in the redfish spec but I agree with Ed that this should be filled in regardless of whether it exists on D-Bus. That is a pattern we have followed in bmcweb, we treat "Status" as if it is required.

https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/PowerSupply.v1_0_0.json
            "required": [
                "@odata.id",
                "@odata.type",
                "Id",
                "Name"
            ],
Done

Please see the existing code for health monitoring within chassis.  This will need to be rolled up.

Also, please avoid the ternary here.  It makes the code harder to read.

PowerSupply is not a sensor. Its health status is determined by Functional, only true or false. True is "OK" and false is "Critical". So I don't think it needs to be rolled up, and it don't need the "HealthPopulate" in health.hpp
